---Sigsum/ST community meet-up

* When: 5-7 May, 2026
* Where: Stockholm, Sweden
* Sign-up: reach out to rgdd@glasklarteknik.se, the number of participants is
  limited and priority will be given to Sigsum/ST/transparency contributors.
  (You can also reach out to others at Glasklar Teknik as you see fit.)

---Overview

We kick off the meet-up with lunch on Tuesday, 1200 CEST.  Feel free to arrive
earlier on Tuesday.  Our venue will be open from 0845 CEST.

We end the meet-up with lunch on Thursday, 1200 CEST.  Feel free to stay longer
during the afternoon.  Our venue will be closed around 1800 CEST.

We will host an open-mic session on Wednesday afternoon, which is then followed
by a social dinner.  The open mic and dinner may include additional guests.

(Open mic slots are ~15m including Q/A.  You can talk about anything you like.
It doesn't have to be technical or work related, but it could be.  In the past,
we've had talks that range from crayfish and home automation to traffic
analysis, transparency, and how to multiply numbers.  There's no need to bring
slides, but you're of course welcome to bring a slide deck if you want.)

The overall agenda is casual, and is best compared to a 2-3 day hallway track in
a location that Glasklar Teknik hosts.  We will have an opening circle each day,
during which we sync on what people are up to (hacking, breakouts, and such).

You will receive more practical information on sign-up.  And if you're curious
about attending but is unsure, reach out and we'll take it from there. :-)
